Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced).

In a #large bowl{}, combine the @breadcrumbs{10%grams}, @salt{1/2%tsp} and @water{1%tbsp} for the breadcrumbs (see pantry for both amounts) along with half the garlic.

Add the @lamb mince{200%grams} to the breadcrumbs, season with @pepper{} and mix together with your hands.

Shape the lamb mixture into mini sausage shapes, 4 per person. Flatten to make koftas.

Pop them onto a #large baking tray{}. When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. The koftas are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Koftas ==

While the koftas bake, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #large frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the onion, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until golden, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, boil a full #kettle{}. Trim the @green beans{80%grams}(trimmed and cut into thirds).

== Couscous ==

Pop the @couscous{120%grams} in a large bowl.

Pour in the @boiled water{200%ml} for the couscous (see pantry for amount), stir in half the @chicken stock paste{20%grams}, then cover tightly with #cling film{}. Leave to the side for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @cider vinegar{15%ml} with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have any). Set aside.

== Sauce ==

Once the onion is golden, add a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} (if you have any), @tomato puree{30%grams}, green beans and the remaining garlic to the pan. Fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Stir through the @water{200%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount) and remaining chicken stock paste. Simmer until the beans are tender and the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once thickened, stir through the @harissa paste{50%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and @honey{1%tbsp}. Remove from the heat.

Add the koftas to the sauce and turn to coat.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, fluff up the couscous. Toss the @baby leaf mix{20%grams} through the dressing.

Share the couscous between your bowls and top with the koftas and harissa sauce.

Serve the baby leaf salad alongside to finish. Enjoy!